description.narrative: A ten-year analysis of child marriage is released to inform policy and programme. Models are supported and implemented on communicating about reproductive health, healthy relationships and marriage which would reach 32 millions members of faith-based women's organizations; on community-based child marriage prevention involving religious and community leaders, life-skill education curriculum that have reached 6000 students. Supports take place in three provinces for scale-up for anti-bullying and positive discipline in schools including islamic boarding schools, with one city allocating fund for replication. Commitment from the Ministry of Education and Culture affirmed to replicate the student-led anti bullying programme. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/07/2020
